    "summary": "I am a Manager, with high energy and enthusiasm. Within a team I feel responsible for achieving results, getting things moving and ensuring a fun, positive ambiance. With 15 years of working experience within Supply Chain Management/ Operations Management, I am very skilled in quickly analysing complex situations and finding the best path forward. I am pragmatic, precise and agile; constantly seeking to further develop myself and my team. My areas of interest are Project Management, Supply Chain Management, Sourcing & Procurement, Change Management, Organization Transformation and Sustainability.\n\nI have done several assignments within various industries: Pharmaceuticals, Consumer Electronics, Chemicals, Steel, Animal Food, Retail, Fertilizer, Banking, Semiconductors and FMCG. The topics varied from Strategic Sourcing, Procurement diagnostic, Organization Transformation, Category Management, Process optimization and implementation, Project Management, Benefit Tracking, Low cost country sourcing and Change Management. At the moment I am focusing on Maintanance Cost control. Ensuring the maintenance budgets for 12 work units.\nFurthermore I am currently coaching a group of 12 technical and maintenance trainees ik their first years of their career. \n\nI've also spend one year in Sierra Leone with Voluntary Services Overseas(VSO) as a Value Chain Advisor for a development project sponsored by the EU/ CARE International.",
